<p>A <b>trade secret</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Formula" title="Formula">formula</a>, <a href="/wiki/Best_practice" title="Best practice">practice</a>, <a href="/wiki/Process" title="Process">process</a>, <a href="/wiki/Design" title="Design">design</a>, <a href="/wiki/Legal_instrument" title="Legal instrument">instrument</a>, <a href="/wiki/Pattern" title="Pattern">pattern</a>, or compilation of <a href="/wiki/Information" title="Information">information</a> which is not generally known or reasonably ascertainable, by which a <a href="/wiki/Business" title="Business">business</a> can obtain an economic advantage over competitors or customers. In some <a href="/wiki/Jurisdiction" title="Jurisdiction">jurisdictions</a>, such secrets are referred to as "confidential information" or "classified information".</p>
